:::summary
Biology is the scientific study of living organisms — from the smallest bacterium to the tallest redwood, from the chemistry of a single cell to the dynamics of a global ecosystem. As the science of life, it stands at the intersection of chemistry, physics, and the deepest questions of existence. For Christians, biology is an exploration of God's most extraordinary work: living creatures made, as Genesis declares, "after their kind," bearing the imprint of a brilliant and purposeful Creator.
:::

